Southern Altai: {{t|alt|эжик}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|puerta|f}}, {{t+|es|postigo|m}} {{qualifier|smaller door on a larger door}}\n* Sranan Tongo: {{tt|srn|doro}}\n* Sumerian: {{tt|sux|𒆍|tr=KA2}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|mlango}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|dörr|c}}, {{tt+|sv|port|c}} {{q|of garage, main entrance of apartment}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt+|tl|pinto}}, {{tt|tl|pintuan}}\n* Tajik: {{tt|tg|дар‍}}, {{t+|tg|боб}}, {{t+|tg|дарвоза}}\n* Talysh: {{tt|tly|بر|tr=bar}}\n* Tamil: {{tt+|ta|கதவு}}\n* Tangut: {{tt|txg|𗐺}}\n* Taos: {{tt|twf|kə̏dénemą}}\n* Tarifit: {{t|rif|tawwurt|f}}\n* Tatar: {{tt+|tt|ишек}}\n* Telugu: {{tt+|te|తలుపు}}, {{tt+|te|ద్వారము}}\n* Thai: {{tt+|th|ประตู}}\n*: Northern Thai: {{tt|nod|ᨸᨲᩪ|tr= pa tǔu}}\n*: Southern Thai: {{tt|sou|ตู}}\n* Tokelauan: {{t|tkl|fāitotoka}}\n* Tibetan: {{tt|bo|སྒོ}}\n* Tigrinya: {{tt|ti|ኣፍደገ}}\n* Tillamook: {{t|til|sƛ̓kə́n}}\n* Tiwi: {{tt|tiw|kunji}}\n* Tocharian A: {{tt|xto|yokäm}}\n* Tocharian B: {{tt|txb|twere}}\n* Tregami: {{tt|trm|dår}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|kapı}}\n* Turkmen: {{tt|tk|gapy}}, {{tt|tk|iişik}}\n* Udmurt: {{tt|udm|ӧс}}\n* Ugaritic: {{tt|uga|𐎄𐎍𐎚}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|две́рі|f-p}}\n* Urdu: {{tt|ur|دَرْوازَہ|m}}, {{tt|ur|دَر|m}} {{qualifier|poetic}}, {{tt|ur|باب|m}} {{qualifier|literary or rare}}, {{t|ur|دوار|m}}\n* Uyghur: {{tt+|ug|ئىشىك}}\n* Uzbek: {{tt+|uz|eshik}}\n* Venetan: {{tt+|vec|pòrta|f}}\n* Veps: {{tt|vep|uksʹ}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|cửa}}\n* Volapük: {{tt+|vo|yan}}\n* Võro: {{tt|vro|uss}}\n* Votic: {{tt|vot|uhsi}}\n* Waigali: {{tt|wbk|dor}}, {{tt|wbk|do}}\n* Wakhi: {{tt|wbl|bar}}\n* Walloon: {{tt+|wa|ouxh|m}}\n* Waray-Waray: {{tt|war|purta}}\n* Warlpiri: {{tt|wbp|ngulya}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|dôr|f}}, {{tt+|cy|drws|m}}\n* Wolaytta: {{t|wal|penggiya}}\n* Wolof: {{tt|wo|bunt}}\n* Wutunhua: {{tt|wuh|men}}\n* Xhosa: {{tt|xh|ucango|c11|c10}}\n* Yaeyama: {{tt|rys|宿|tr=やどぅ, yadu}}\n* Yaghnobi: {{tt|yai|давар|tr=davar}}\n* Yakut: {{tt|sah|аан}}\n* Yiddish: {{tt|yi|טיר|f}}\n* Yonaguni: {{tt|yoi|宿|tr=だどぅ, dadu}}\n* Yoruba: {{tt|yo|ìlẹ̀kùn}}\n* Yup'ik: {{tt|esu|amiik}}\n* Yurok: {{tt|yur|ɂeksoɂ}}\n* Zazaki: {{tt+|zza|çêber|m}}, {{tt+|zza|kêber|m}}, {{tt+|zza|ber|m}}\n* Zhuang: {{tt|za|dou}}\n* Zulu: {{tt+|zu|isicabha|c7|c8}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|any flap that opens like a door}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t+|af|deur}}\n* Danish: {{tt|da|låge|c}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|luukku}}; {{tt+|fi|ovi}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|anta|f}}, {{tt|it|antina|f}}, {{tt+|it|sportello|m}}\n* Sotho: {{t|st|lemati}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|lucka|c}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|gümrük kapısı}}\n* Zazaki: {{tt|zza|macelığ|m}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|immigration: entry point}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|portti}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|figurative: means of approach or access}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|portti}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|figurative: barrier}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|raja}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|computing: software mechanism for interacting with a remotely running program}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|cycling}} {{lb|en|transitive|cycling}} To cause a [[collision#Noun|collision]] by opening the door of a vehicle in front of an [[oncoming#Adjective|oncoming]] [[cyclist#Noun|cyclist]] or [[pedestrian#Noun|pedestrian]].\n#* {{RQ:Guardian|author=Helen Pidd|title=I got 'doored' while undertaking on my bike. Was it my fault?|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20230815141137/http://www.theguardian.com/environment/bike-blog/2018/feb/06/i-got-doored-while-undertaking-on-my-bike-was-it-my-fault|date=6 February 2018|passage=Kerr has acted for numerous clients who have been '''doored''', including one man knocked off his bike and on to spiked railings, and another who ended up hitting a tree.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Ben Spurr|title=How an Ontario rule stops 'doored' cyclists from getting drivers' insurance info|work=w:Toronto Star|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/how-an-ontario-rule-stops-doored-cyclists-from-getting-drivers-insurance-info/article_feb75ac5-ea06-5870-9880-bc7b0054f1da.html|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/Q2gxa|archivedate=27 April 2024|location=Toronto, Ont.|publisher=w:Toronto Star Newspapers Ltd.|date=15 December 2019|issn=0319-0781|oclc=1081127642|passage=He [Pete Karageorgos] said cyclists who are '''doored''' are entitled to claim accident benefits from the driver's insurer if they aren't covered by a policy of their own.}}\n#* {{RQ:LATimes|author=Angie Orellana Hernandez|title=Being doored to death is a cyclist's nightmare. How can it be prevented?|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240422034231/https://www.latimes.com/california/story/2023-12-19/what-is-dooring-the-bicyclist-collision-that-killed-a-hollywood-producer|date=19 December 2023|passage=To avoid being '''doored''', cyclists such as Vilain, Davis-Overstreet and Michael Schneider monitor as many telltale signs as possible: shadows, brake lights, the actions of people sitting in the driver's seat.}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|doorer|dooring<qq:noun>}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|to cause a collision by opening the door of a vehicle in front of an oncoming cyclist or pedestrian}}{{multitrans|data=\n* French: {{tt+|fr|emportiérer}}\n* Hungarian: {{t|hu|[[rányit]]ja az [[ajtó]]t}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=door|Rood|ordo|oord|rood|O'Dor|odor}}\n\n{{cln|en|terms with open-syllable lengthening of Middle English /i u/}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/doːr/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-door.ogg}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|door}}\n* {{rhymes|nl|oːr|s=1}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymid|nl|through}}\n{{root|nl|ine-pro|*terh₂-}}\nFrom {{inh|nl|dum|dōre}}, from {{inh|nl|odt|thuro}}, from {{inh|nl|gem-pro|*þurhw}}.\n\n====Preposition====\n{{head|nl|preposition}}\n\n# [[through]]\n#: {{ux|nl|Hij schoot de bal '''door''' het raam.|He kicked the ball '''through''' the window.}}\n# [[across]], [[around]] {{gloss|within a certain space}}\n#: {{ux|nl|Dolenthousiast rende het hondje '''door''' de kamer.|Very enthusiastically the puppy ran '''around''' the room.}}\n# [[because of]], [[due to]]\n#: {{syn|nl|vanwege|ten gevolge van}}\n#: {{ux|nl|'''Door''' files kan ik niet op tijd komen.|'''Because of''' traffic jams I'm unable to arrive on time.}}\n# [[by]], by means of\n#: {{ux|nl|Hij vermeed een confrontatie '''door''' de andere kant op te lopen.|He avoided a confrontation '''by''' walking the other way.}}\n\n=====Declension=====\n{{nl-pronadv-table|door}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|nl\n|door-\n|doordat\n|door middel van\n}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|af|deur}}\n* {{desc|brc|doro}}\n* {{desc|gmw-jdt|dœr}}\n* {{desc|dcr|door}}\n* {{desc|pey|door}}\n* {{desc|skw|door}}\n* {{desc|srn|doro}}\n** {{desc|djk|doo}}\n** {{desc|kww|doo|doro}}\n** {{desc|srm|dóu}}\n** {{desc|car|dorome|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|jvn|dhur|dhur-dhuran}}\n* {{desc|pap|dor|bor=1}}\n\n====Adverb====\n{{nl-adv}}\n\n# [[through]]\n# [[forward]], [[on]]\n#: {{ux|nl|Ondanks slecht weer ging het feest toch '''door.'''|Despite bad weather, the party went '''on''' anyway.}}\n# {{lb|nl|postpositional|directional}} [[through]] (implying motion)\n#: {{ux|nl|Ik rijd nu de stad '''door'''.|I'm now driving '''through''' the city.}}\n# {{lb|nl|postpositional|spatial}} [[across]], [[around]] {{gloss|within a certain space}}\n#: {{ux|nl|Dolenthousiast rende het hondje de kamer '''door'''.|Very enthusiastically the puppy ran '''around''' the room.}}\n# {{lb|nl|postpositional|temporal}} [[throughout]], [[round]] {{gloss|occurring all the time – constantly or frequently – within a certain time period}}\n#: {{ux|nl|Zij kon geen maaltijd meer binnenhouden en moest de hele dag '''door''' kleine beetjes eten.|She was unable to keep a meal in her stomach anymore and had to eat little snacks '''throughout''' the day.}}\n#: {{ux|nl|Het hele jaar '''door''' waren er problemen met hooligans.|There were problems with hooligans all year '''round'''.}}\n#: {{ux|nl|De kinderen waren de hele vakantie '''door''' in het zwembad te vinden.|The children could be seen at the swimming pool '''throughout''' the holidays.}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|nl\n|doorbreken\n|doordraaien\n|doorgaan\n|doorgang\n|doorgeven\n|doorhalen\n|doorknippen\n|doorleren\n|doorlopen\n|doornemen\n|doorslaan\n|doorstart\n|doorstrepen\n|doortocht\n|doorvoeren\n|doorwerken\n|doorzetten\n|doorzichtig\n|tussendoor\n}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|af|deur}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{etymid|nl|fool}}\nFrom {{inh|nl|dum|dôre}}, from {{inh|nl|odt|*dōro}}, {{inh|nl|gmw-pro|*dauʀō}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{nl-noun|m|-en|-}}\n\n# {{lb|nl|now|Southern Dutch|archaic}} [[fool]], [[moron]]\n#* '''1869''', Frans de Cort, \"Walter van de Vogelweide als paedagoog\" (article including a poem), in Frans de Cort (ed.), ''De toekomst. Tijdschrift voor opvoeding en onderwijs'', Vol. 3, No. 6, page 245.\n#*: {{quote|nl|Past ook op uwe ooren / Beter dan de '''doren'''!}}\n#: {{syn|nl|dwaas|nar|zot}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n* {{l|nl|dwaas}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{l|nl|oord}}, {{l|nl|rood}}\n\n{{cln|nl|postpositional adverbs}}\n\n==Old Galician-Portuguese==\n{{was fwotd|roa-opt|2012|October|14}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|roa-opt|:inh|la:dolor<alt:dolōrem><t:pain>|text=+}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|roa-opt|/do.ˈoɾ/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{roa-opt-noun|f|pl=doores}}\n\n# [[pain]]\n#* {{roa-opt-cite-cantigas|E|206|text=⁊ untou lle bẽ a chaga<br>⁊ perdeu Log a '''door'''.<br>⁊ poſſ el a ſua mão.<br>ben firme en ſeu logar|translation=And anointed well the wound<br>and soon the '''pain''' was gone.<br>And put his hand<br>very firmly in its place.}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|roa-opt|doorida}}, {{l|roa-opt|doorido}}\n* {{l|roa-opt|doorosa}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|gl|dor|g=f}}\n* {{desc|pt|dor|g=f}} {{see desc}}\n\n==Scots==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|sco|dour}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{dercat|sco|gem-pro|ine-pro|inh=2}}\nFrom {{inh|sco|enm|dore}}, {{m|enm|dor}}, from {{inh|sco|ang|duru||door}}, {{m|ang|dor||gate}}, from {{inh|sco|gmw-pro|*dur}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|sco|[duːr]}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sco-noun|p=doors}}\n\n# {{l|en|door}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:DSL}}\n\n==Somali==\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|so|verb}}\n\n# to [[choose]]"}}